[Black "Chapter 1 Classical Formation"]

{In the classical formation after ...Nc6, d6, a6 and Nf6, Black threatens to halt White's momentum with ...Bg4. White can choose between 8. Bf4 and the adventurous, Evans-style b4.}

1. e4 c5 2. d4 cxd4 3. c3 dxc3 4. Nxc3 Nc6 5. Nf3 d6 6. Bc4 a6 (6... Nf6 7. e5 dxe5 8. Qxd8+ Nxd8 (8... Kxd8 9. Ng5) 9. Nb5 Rb8 10. Nc7+ (10. Nxe5 e6) 10... Kd7 11. Nb5 Nc6? (11... e6) 12. Bf4) 7. O-O Nf6 {[%entry]} (7... Bg4? 8. Bxf7+) 8. Bf4 (8. b4!? Bg4 9. b5 axb5 (9... Bxf3 10. gxf3 Ne5 11. bxa6) (9... Ne5? 10. Nxe5 dxe5 11. Qb3 e6 (11... Bh5 12. bxa6 (12. Rd1) 12... bxa6 13. Bxa6) 12. h3 Bh5 13. g4) 10. Nxb5 e6 11. Bf4) (8. h3?! e6) 8... Bg4 (8... e5 9. Ng5 exf4 10. Nxf7) (8... b5 9. Bxf7+ Kxf7 10. e5) (8... g6 9. e5) 9. h3 Bxf3 (9... Bh5 10. g4 Bg6 11. Qe2) 10. Qxf3 e6 11. Rfd1 *

